comment: [Detectable with stop watch] RATR shows that Tucker (TOR) never fully clears the lane and is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Lowry (TOR) makes contact with Morris (DET) that affects his FOM.
Valanciunas (TOR) makes marginal contact with Morris (DET) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Detectable with stop watch] Drummond (DET) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
[Observable in enhanced video] RATR shows Harris (DET) move his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Morris (DET) moves his pivot foot.
Drummond (DET) makes incidental contact with Valanciunas (TOR) that does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
DeRozan (TOR) makes marginal contact with Smith (DET) that does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Morris (DET) unnaturally extends his leg into Tucker (TOR) and initiates the contact.
Drummond (DET) kicks the ball after the made basket, which prevents the opposing team from quickly inbounding the ball.
Ibaka (TOR) legally contests Smith's (DET) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Valanciunas (TOR) briefly grasps Drummond's (DET) jersey, but the contact does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Morris (DET) legally contests DeRozan's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) makes incidental contact with DeRozan (TOR) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] RHH shows DeRozan (TOR) move his pivot foot heel to toe. The officials are looking for any illegal contact and do not pick up the pivot foot.
Smith (DET) commits a take foul on Valanciunas (TOR).
DeRozan (TOR) initiates the marginal contact with Morris (DET) during the inbound.
Harris (DET) commits a take foul on Valanciunas (TOR).
Ibaka (TOR) legally contests Caldwell-Pope's (DET) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
DeRozan (TOR) legally contests Harris' (DET) jump shot attempt.
